title: The Puars - After the Party [1999]
description:
Review by Heather Phares
Boston's Push Stars make their major-label debut with After the Party. After a speedy rise to prominence, which included the release of two indie albums, appearing on the There's Something About Mary soundtrack, and winning the title of 1997's Best Unsigned Band in America, the group shows off their penetrating pop skills here. Produced by Jack Joseph and Gavin MacKillop, the Push Stars' sound is radio-friendly and smart. (3/5)
